N2  - This paper implements Industry 4.0 technologies to Agritech Business 4.0. I4.0 Technologies are mapped with Agritech Business 4.0 key elements such as crop management, soil management, pest and disease management, water conservation, protection of farmers health, increased productivity, food safety, supply chain and strengthening the connect between urban and rural areas. We have shown that how agriculture and food distribution network cannot be handled with just one technology to manage all processes. As long as IOT and DLT can be combined, it can manage the whole process of Agritech Business 4.0 development to the fullest extent possible. Cyber Physical Agri system is proposed to illustrate this. Referring to the United Nations sustainable development goals (SDG), our research work directly addresses sub-goals 2.3 and 2.4 (End hunger, achieve food security and improved nutrition and promote sustainable agriculture).
