N2  - Digital platforms have pervaded every sector and industry. These digital platforms are information technology-enabled services (ITES) modelthat have facilitated the transactions for all kinds of businesses and services. They act as an interface between the transacting agents and signify a bridging link. The connection of healthcare services with digital technology has existed since decades but its popularity has increased recently. Healthcare is an important sector during all time frames and it never goes through a sluggish phase, be it any economic recession or warfare. The chapter is based on seminal research, which is both descriptive and analytical in nature, and highlights the various facets of digitalization in healthcare sector through secondary data sources. Crucial findings indicate that the healthcare market is expected to reach 372 billion USD in India by end of year 2022. Digital penetration is swift and steep in healthcare primarily covering all five segments including the hospitals, diagnostics services, pharmaceutical, medical/surgical supplies, and insurance. Patients nowadays are not only well educated but also have better awareness regarding health. Factors like rising incomes and access to insurance to all strata of society has helped improve access to quality health services. Digitalization of healthcare services is also increasing along with the rapid increase in Internet accessibility. The May 2020 data indicates that the overall internet penetration in India increased to 41% with 574 million active internet users which is a 24% increase from the previous year, 2019. The Government of India (GOI) sponsored Digital India campaign has added the healthcare sector as the National Digital Health Mission aims to boost the online accessibility of health to all with a proposal to increase public health spending to 2.5% of GDP by 2025, which is still quite small considering the vast population. The chapter covers the contemporary developments and suggests new avenues that can make the healthcare sector more pervasive, accessible, economical and affordable, within the outreach of all sections of society with the use of digital technology.
ER  - 
