N2  - Accelerating the pace of information technology development encourages companies to transform their digitally business processes in order to conduct effective cross-industry interaction between market participants (suppliers, consumers of goods, works, and services). The relevance of the study is because the development of modern digital capabilities has led to a change in the system of communications, transactions, the economic thinking of consumers and people's relationships that are being transformed. The financial sector needs further development of the banking theoretical aspectsin the context of the transition to a new "digital transformation"paradigm and systematization of the accumulated experience in order to improve the methods of bank management, taking into account the global instability in the world. In the existing system that is represented by banks of Russia, digital transformation is characterized by the development of Fintech ecosystem. The main task of Fintech ecosystemis rethinking the architecture of providing financial services through customer data analytics; automation of the bank's main business processes through the introduction of artificial intelligence; precise distribution of the personnel potential of the bank's employees; protection of online services, personal data, ensuring information security of banks.
