N2  - In this paper, a power grid digital twin model operation control method is studied. First, model registration, publication and management are established to establish the basis for the management and analysis of power grid digital twin model and further application. Secondly, the real-time operation monitoring of the twin model is studied, and the security attributes of visibility and controllability are proposed. Finally, the twin model resource scheduling is studied. All kinds of digitalized resources involved in power grid digital twin, such as model resources, tool resources, data resources and computing resources, are realized through the coordination of service layer, tool layer and application layer. Through the development of functions such as multi-dimensional model management, model knowledge base management, multi-dimensional visual display, and operation operation, model services such as model registration and release, operation and operation, and status monitoring are provided to support the application of models in different scenarios.
