UR  - https://doi.org/10.1145/3629378.3629458
N2  - Enterprise digital transformation and green innovation are two important contents to realize China's long-term development strategy in the future. There is a relationship of mutual influence and promotion between the two. How to better promote green innovation through enterprise digitalization needs to be discussed. This paper selects enterprise dynamic capability as a mediating variable and divides it into innovation ability, learning absorption ability, and adaptability. Taking the A-share listed companies in the manufacturing industry from 2015 to 2020 as the research object, this paper discusses the mediating role of the three aspects of dynamic capabilities in the impact of digital transformation on green innovation. Based on the empirical data analysis, it is found that the digital transformation of enterprises can significantly promote the green innovation of enterprises, and the dynamic capability of enterprises plays an important intermediary role in it, and the intermediary effect of enterprise learning absorptive capacity is the strongest, indicating that the improvement of the digital level of enterprises can strengthen the dynamic capability of enterprises, and then enhance the green innovation ability of enterprises.
