N2  - The financial technology industry is undergoing a transformation as a result of the increased usage of artificial intelligence (AI) in financial trading. New developments in artificial intelligence-driven trading systems are investigated in this study. Particular attention is paid to the ways in which these systems might be utilized in predictive analytics, portfolio optimization, high-frequency trading, and market sentiment analysis. By utilizing artificial intelligence techniques such as machine learning, deep learning, and natural language processing, these systems exhibit an accuracy and efficiency that is unmatched in the industry. Additionally, the paper covers significant obstacles, such as data quality, regulatory compliance, ethical considerations, and market stability. Additionally, the article presents future directions in explainable artificial intelligence, blockchain integration, and quantum computing. These findings highlight the potential for artificial intelligence to bring about a transformation in global financial markets.
