N2  - Therefore, the purpose of this research paper is to put into light the implication of using quantum computing for the enhancement of the likelihood of network security and encryption. Challenges for conventional cryptography are immense in the framework of quantum technology, that is why construction of quantum-safe cryptography, as well as enhanced QKD is necessary. It also provides an overview of various quantumresistant cryptographic algorithms of which are lattice-based, hash-based, and multivariate quadratic one, on the aspects of efficiency, security, and probable areas of concern in the real world. In addition, it offers fresh viewpoints about one-party BB84 and E91 QKD protocols on the enhancement of secure communication while using quantum ideas. In the light of the approaches towards the paradigm, the lattice-based algorithms provide a reasonable degree of protection against wastage of time/effort and the hash-based and the MQ based algorithms have their pluses and minuses. This is not to say that via QKD protocols the dream of secure communication is a remote one; rather it is more a case that the difficulties in putting it into practice are less theoretical and lie more firmly in the realms of cost and distance. Hence it can be seen that although quantum computing has the capability to develop new improved features of the network security there are technical challenges and concern which needs to be resolve to reap the set benefits. More future research and development will be necessary for implementing the quantum technologies for enhancing the encryption techniques and making the communication secure to adapt the emerging model.
