N2  - This paper presents a Quantum Resistant Identity and Access Management (IAM) System tailored for enterprise deployments to mitigate the emerging risk posed by quantum-capable adversaries to classical public-key cryptography. The system integrates NIST-aligned post-quantum cryptographic primitives, a Zero-Trust policy engine, multi-factor and biometric authentication, behavioral analytics driven by machine learning, and a quantum-safe blockchain-based audit trail. Implemented with a React + TypeScript frontend and a Supabase (PostgreSQL) backend, the design prioritizes modularity, scalability, and standards compliance. We describe the system architecture, key modules (cryptographic layer, zero-trust engine, authentication and authorization layers, and governance services), and a testing methodology that includes quantum-attack simulation, behavioral anomaly detection, and performance benchmarking. Experimental validation on a prototype demonstrates acceptable authentication latency, sub-100 ms trust score evaluation, and quantum-resistant key generation within practical bounds for enterprise use. Comparative analysis shows the solution provides unique quantum-resilience and integrated governance advantages against mainstream IAM offerings. We conclude with a roadmap for QKD integration, FIDO2 hardware token support, and AI-driven governance for continued robustness as quantum capabilities evolve.
