N2  - In this paper, it is proposed to ensure the reinforced IoT security principles are given, by applying the business backgrounds in addition to these for which the improved detection devises and of edge encryption algorithms are made use with the facilitation of the artificial intelligence-based procedures for the mitigation of the cyber-physical attacks in the reality. When compared to traditionalist architectures, in which, predominantly security is a static need that must be addressed, our proposed platform is very much dynamic in the sense that it properly co-relates enterprise risk strategies to basic adaptative AI-driven policy enforcement as well as cryptographic processing at the device level. It is leveraging small transformer models in a way to learn the probable threats, and appropriately using federated edge learning mechanisms, to ensure that privacy is preserved around end-points and appropriate decisions at extreme low latency are taken. In our proposal, we combine post-quantum encryption standards such that compromising windows can be taken well below 200 milliseconds in order to provide robust data security. The proposed method is validated under a properly designed simulation environment of an industrial automation network using diverse/heterogeneous IoT nodes, which means, achieving an average threat detection accuracy of 94.6 percent and reduced transmission overhead of 42 percent when actually compared with all the centralized approaches. Experiences demonstrate that effects of adversarial inference resistance and zero day attacks resilience, together can be accomplished only when security is connected with those enforced against all possible operational business objectives, mostly like: uptime dependability, and tracceability of compliance. The study will make practical architectural advanced solutions of trust compatible with, from the theoretical point of view, trust models and practical systems for securing the IoT systems they can be applied with an eventually deployed.
