N2  - The complexity of distributed infrastructures, multi-tenancy and common advancement of sophisticated cyber-attacks all contribute to growing threats to cloud computing environments. Conventional security solutions are frequently ineffective in handling mezzo-day attacks, insiders and vulnerabilities of quantum kind. In an attempt to counter these shortcomings, this paper introduces new mitigation method in Intelligent Quantum-Resilient Adaptive Defense Mechanism (IQ-ADM). Proposed reinforcement tool integrates the deep reinforcement learning into the tool to permit adaptive and independent threat detection with the emergence and homomorphic encryption may secure privacy with analytics across many nodes. In addition, quantum-safe cryptography primitives are added in such a way that, to provide resilience to attacks by future quantum computing. The system relies on the concept of federated learning to analyze user behavior, traffic patterns, and infrastructure utilization without sharing valuable raw information and therefore offer an ideal balance of safety and consistency. It employs a trust management layer, used as a blockchain boosts data integrity and responsibility in the communications between the nodes and a dynamic policy engine, powered by game-theoretic optimal assignment of defensive resources. IQ-ADM provides an upgradable cryptography defense system that can sustain the key workloads of the existing cloud eco-sphere with the advantages of state-current adaptive intelligence. The outcomes indicate that this solution is a solution to the major security issues, as the protection is solid and will withstand under the fluctuating and risky conditions in cloud computing environments. The suggested framework attains an overall accuracy of 96.2% proving its efficacy in secure cloud computing settings.
