N2  - The rising sophistication of cyber threats targeting critical financial infrastructure necessitates a paradigm shift in risk management and cybersecurity defenses. This paper introduces the Q-DTN framework, integrating Quantum Machine Learning (QML) and Decentralized Trust Networks (DTNs) to safeguard financial systems from advanced persistent threats and data breaches. Key contributions include the Quantum-Enhanced Risk Classifier (QERC), a hybrid QML algorithm for real-time threat detection, paired with a blockchain-based DTN for secure data sharing. An Explainable Quantum AI (XQAI) module ensures compliance. Simulations on financial datasets show 97% fraud detection accuracy with zero data exposure, a 5% improvement over classical methods with 98% less overhead, affirming Q-DTN's potential for production use.
