N2  - 6G, a new generation of mobile networks, is about to be introduced. In 2030, this will enable the Internet of Everything (IOE) and bring about a spectacular revolution in communications technology. While some research teams have already started projects on 6G, many nations are still working on 5G, and B5G has not yet been developed. High, cutting-edge operating quality will be provided by 6G, for instance in holographic and virtual reality communication. Predicting the specifics of 6G and the key technologies that will distinguish it is challenging at this stage. A new technology, 6G, has emerged as a result of widespread ICT applications like IoT, AI, blockchain, extended reality (XR), and virtual reality (VR). 6G, which builds on 5G technology, will significantly affect deep, smart, holographic, and ubiquitous connectivity. Particular attention should be paid to the difficulties and problems associated with 6G. A number of options should be explored in order to meet the demands of 6G users. There are many obstacles to overcome. This study highlights the differences between 5G and 6G, as well as the issues that 5G has not been able to resolve. The article also discusses potential difficulties that could prevent the deployment of 6G. To establish the state of 6G technology for further research, we define its key potential features. This review provides a brief discussion of technological perspectives, challenges and related issues. We also introduce the 6G framework and technology breakdown. We clarified applications and future directions.
