N2  - In the present work, the computer revolution is witnessed by surveying the literature based on experiments and hypothesis on how quantum computing may improve imaging, diagnosis, therapy, and population health. The healthcare industry is advancing quickly with innovation. Quantum computing and metaverse are developing advances that are likely to revolutionize the healthcare domain. Quantum computing has the potential to enhance the implementation of personalized pharmaceuticals and improve diagnostics. On the other hand, metaverse holds a guarantee in changing the way healthcare administrations are conveyed and how patients get connected with healthcare suppliers. This research study provides an outline of quantum computing's current state and metaverse innovation in healthcare & pharmaceutical industry, counting the different applications and utilizing cases. This research study investigates how quantum computing can help in genomics and clinical inquiry, diagnostics, and image restoration, whereas the metaverse can offer telemedicine, persistent checking, and preparing. Moreover, this research study examines the challenges and impediments of these innovations and the long- haul scope for their selection in healthcare. According to our study, advances in quantum computing and the metaverse might revolutionize the pharmaceutical and healthcare industries in the future by delivering high-quality, low-cost, and individualized treatment to people all over the world.
