N2  - Digital intellectual property rights (IPR) management in cyberspace faces numerous challenges, including cross-border enforcement complexities, fair use ambiguities, and emerging technology disputes. This study proposes a Cognitive-Analytical Framework integrating doctrinal and empirical approaches with advanced technologies such as artificial intelligence (AI) and blockchain to enhance IPR enforcement. Using survey data, case studies, and scenario-based simulations, the framework demonstrated its effectiveness in resolving key issues. The refined framework improved infringement detection accuracy from 85% to 92%, reduced dispute resolution time by 22% (from 7.4 to 5.8 months), and increased stakeholder satisfaction from 73% to 89%. Technologies like image recognition AI and blockchain were found to be highly effective, achieving simulated effectiveness of 93% and 87%, respectively. Legal text mining revealed that fair use disputes (34%) and cross-border issues (29%) are the most frequent challenges. The results validate the proposed framework's ability to address diverse IPR challenges while promoting harmonized global standards. This study paves the way for future integration of quantum encryption and predictive analytics to further enhance digital IPR management.
