N2  - Blockchain technology integration in healthcare has become a game-changing strategy to solve important issues with safe data exchange. In order to ensure data quality, openness, and privacy, this article investigates a blockchain-based architecture for safe and scalable data sharing in the healthcare industry. The suggested architecture makes use of encryption methods, consensus processes, and smart contracts to facilitate safe stakeholder communication. Modular features designed for real-time auditing, access control, and interoperability are introduced in the suggested model. Datasets that replicate patient records and medical transactions are part of the implementation, and they have been verified by thorough performance measurements. The study highlights how blockchain can be used to solve practical problems like privacy concerns, interoperability problems, and data breaches. The suggested architecture guarantees the security, accessibility, and reliability of critical healthcare data by utilizing sophisticated algorithms such as SHA-256, Merkle Trees, and smart contract-based RBAC. By combining these technologies, a strong answer to contemporary healthcare problems is offered, setting the stage for future developments like AI-powered analytics and Internet of Things-enabled monitoring systems. When compared to conventional systems, the results show increased user trust, security, and efficiency. This study offers a roadmap for next advancements and opens the door for safe, scalable blockchain-enabled healthcare systems.
ER  - 
