N2  - With the rollout of 5th generation (5th generation) wireless networks, academics from all over the world have started to focus on the potential difficulties that might emerge in the beyond B5th generation future. In addition to many other important advantages, 5th generation networks are predicted to bring a surge in the no. of without wire device that are linked as well as the kinds of use cases that might result in network resource constraint. mMTC services have contributed to some of these problems, & it will need a lot of research & innovation to maintain the transition to Enhanced-mMTC with movable network will costs in sixth-generation wireless network. This research provides a framework for 6G networks using two cutting-edge technologies, namely non-coherent communication & backscatter communication, to address the anticipated vast connection requirements with optimal power & spectral efficiency coupled with low hardware cost (BsC). In consideration of the coherence in this technology & their combined ability to provide e-mMTC services in the B5th generation era, a thorough assessment will be done. Other new 6G technologies are also recognized as having a common range of not so-coherent & BsC, with the technologies examined including communications (VLC) & UAV-assisted communications [1].
