N2  - Cow plays an inevitable role in the life of human beings. Generally, homes in rural portion of India mainly depend on cow and its milk products. The responsibility of human is to take immense care on cows. Hence, monitoring of cow health is very much required for the welfare of farmers. Recent researches concentrate on cow health monitoring for improved productivity. If the location of cow is traced by a particular person, that person may try to steal the cow. A secure based arrangement for consistent monitoring of cow health and its accurate location is proposed. The health data of cow is monitored, processed and then forwarded through means of cloud. The sensors are employed to obtain the health information and communicated over the cloud. This precise information is forwarded to the farmers working in the remote place. Block chain technology is implemented in this system for accessing the data in a secure manner.
