N2  - Advanced Persistent Threats (APTs) represent a critical cybersecurity challenge due to their stealth, persistence, and sophisticated evasion capabilities. This paper introduces a novel framework combining hierarchical honeypot architectures with machine learning-driven analytics for early APT detection. Our approach implements low-, medium-, and high-interaction honeypots in segmented network zones, reinforced with honeytokens and protected via honeywalls. Real-world deployments demonstrate 96% detection rates through adaptive behavioral analysis of attacker Tactics, Techniques, Procedures, including zero-day exploits and lateral movement patterns. The system integrates automated log correlation with threat intelligence feeds, addressing key challenges in noise reduction and evasion resistance. Case studies from industrial control and cloud environments validate the framework’s effectiveness as both a detection mechanism and an intelligence gathering platform. We further explore future directions in blockchain-enhanced deception networks and quantum-resistant encryption for next-generation APT defense.
