N2  - This paper examines the integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in the real estate investment domain, with particular emphasis on its potential to improve portfolio optimization through enhanced data integration, predictive accuracy, and advanced risk assessment. AI enables the identification of hidden patterns, demand forecasting, and more precise decision-making in a sector characterized by complex interdependencies and extensive datasets. At the same time, the adoption of AI introduces new cybersecurity risks that are subtle, multifaceted, and often difficult to detect. Such risks threaten the fundamental objectives of information security - confidentiality, integrity, and availability - and may arise during both the development and deployment of AI models. To illustrate possible responses, the paper highlights mitigation strategies noted in recent literature and emphasizes the importance of adopting transparent, adaptive, and risk-aware practices within the real estate sector. Finally, it points to advanced technologies, including blockchain and quantum-based methods, as potential enablers of greater resilience and security in AI-driven real estate investment.
