N2  - An intrusion is an unauthorized activity that causes security breaches, data breaches, financial loss and service disruptions to information in a computer network. Traditional intrusion detection systems (IDS) are not very attractive to secure a network because of its high false alarm rate and difficult intrusion detection for unknown files. Therefore, this research presents an intrusion detection system based on AI using the brood behavior of ants by Ant Colony Optimization (ACO). They were able to improve those detection rates by taking network traffic patterns from the KDD dataset. Although ACO is susceptible to stagnating in local optima, yet its ability to outperform attack scenarios remains small. Artificial Bee Colony (ABC) is inducted to attain convergence to global optima to overcome this. By improving the accuracy of classification, a hybrid approach combining with swarm optimized Artificial Neural Networks is taken. With the developed ACO based IDS, specificity and sensitivity are improved, however, the intrusion detection rates are greater than traditional methods. The detection of this system is effective enough to deal with many attack types, providing good network security.
