N2  - In this era of informatization, network technology has been widely applied, so various regions are gradually strengthening the informatization of financial systems. With the acceleration of China's fiscal informatization process, financial security issues in the network environment are becoming increasingly prominent. Therefore, people must conduct indepth research on the network security issues existing in the current financial system and develop effective travel strategies. Only in this way can the security and safety of the financial system be improved, ensuring the security of network information within the financial system. This article proposed a financial network security situational awareness model based on Bayesian network algorithm. By establishing a Bayesian network model and combining real-time monitoring and data analysis, real-time identification and prediction of financial network security risks can be carried out to improve the security and stability of financial systems. The experimental results showed that the Bayesian network algorithm had the lowest number of false positives, which was 5. The number of false positives for support vector machines and decision trees was slightly higher, at 10 and 13, respectively. This model can effectively identify network security threats and provide an effective security situational awareness method for financial institutions.
