N2  - Cloud-based SaaS platforms like Google Drive and Dropbox enhance collaboration but pose significant security and compliance risks due to dynamic file activities and permission changes. This paper introduces a real-time monitoring framework that intercepts SaaS traffic, extracts detailed file metadata, and stores it in a Pinecone vector database to enable version comparison and anomaly detection. The system uses Presidio and Python scripts to automatically analyze files with changed permissions or content, identifying the presence of sensitive data. AI-driven sensitivity scoring and metadata-based access control tracking allow for precise classification of risks. All changes are logged and forwarded to a centralized syslog server for auditing. A live web dashboard provides visual insights into file-user relationships, role-based access patterns, and suspicious activity trends. By combining real-time traffic interception, vector similarity search, and automated sensitivity detection, the framework offers enhanced visibility, governance, and security across hybrid cloud environments.
