N2  - In the quickly developing scene of smart cities, cyber security has turned into a foremost concern. The joining of innovation and information driven arrangements into metropolitan framework has brought exceptional productivity and comfort, yet it has likewise presented smart cities to new weaknesses. This theoretical presents a high-level investigation of state-of-the-art online protection arrangements intended to hoist the versatility of smart cities. As metropolitan regions proceed to develop and change into complex environments, they face diverse dangers, going from cyber-attacks that can upset basic administrations to information penetration that compromises resident protection. This study digs into the difficulties presented by these dangers and offers an extensive examination of creative cyber security approaches customized to the novel necessities of smart cities. The exploration incorporates a diverse methodology, including the improvement of cutting-edge danger recognition frameworks, the usage of man-made brainpower and AI for prescient online protection, and the foundation of secure correspondence networks for smart metropolises. Moreover, it explores the mix of block chain innovation for changeless information stockpiling and character confirmation, upgrading the general security stance of metropolitan conditions. By breaking down contextual analyses from driving smart metropolises and network safety drives, this study gives significant experiences into fruitful techniques and best practices. Moreover, it investigates the job of public-private associations, administrative systems, and local area commitment in building metropolitan versatility against cyber threats.
