N2  - With the popularization of cloud computing model, the outsourcing of data storage and computing services has become an indispensable trend, which lead to the related data security and privacy protection issues that have attracted extensive attention in the industry. Fully homomorphic encryption, as an encryption technology that can process ciphertext information without exposing plaintext information, has natural user data security and privacy protection characteristics. Meanwhile, the excellent quantum-resistant performance and homomorphic properties of lattice ciphers have made lattice-based homomorphic encryption schemes a much-attend research hotspot in the field of cryptography in recent years. In this paper we mainly introduce the status of all-pass encryption and several typical references for the research of lattice-based all-homomorphic cryptography.
