N2  - 6G, the next-generation Internet of Things, is expected to revolutionize the future of wireless communication systems. This review examines the critical challenges and technological innovations that will shape the 6G landscape, with particular emphasis on the integration of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, coverage solutions, energy efficiency, sustainability, and security frameworks. The analysis reveals that these technologies will be fundamental in enabling 6G networks to process the huge amounts of data generated by connected devices, facilitating real-time network optimization and the development of intelligent and autonomous systems. The integration of AI-driven sustainable network management architectures shows promising results in significantly reducing the environmental impact of future networks. The potential of 6G to be a more intelligent, sustainable, and secure network than its predecessors is highlighted.
