N2  - The convergence of blockchain technology with artificial intelligence is giving rise to a new standard for modern financial management. Through an examination of both the theoretical and practical aspects, this paper delves into the potential revolutionary possibilities of improved blockchain security measures. The method uses historical financial data, blockchain metrics, and AI models to provide a thorough foundation for empirical validation. Machine learning model accuracy and recall rates were enhanced, transaction processing times were shortened, and the number of fraud instances dropped significantly. Improving transactional efficiency, creating reliable predictive analytics, fortifying the financial ecosystem, and expanding financial services are all examples of real-world consequences. Experts, legislators, and scholars attempting to make sense of the intricate digital financial environment will find some useful pointers in the last section. The next stages include research into ethics, legislation changes, decentralised financing, empirical validation, and scalability. A more secure, efficient, and easily accessible international monetary system is the goal of this paper, which offers recommendations for enhancing blockchain security protocols.
