N2  - The fast improvement of quantum computing technology has been the starting point of both excitement and apprehension across various industries. This review paper explores the intricate interplay between block chain technology, quantum cryptography along with post quantum cryptography to resist the quantum computers, focusing on their congregating paths and the implications for the future of secure and decentralized systems. Block chain, foreshadowed for its potential to reform trust and data integrity, relies on cryptographic primitives that could be fundamentally challenged by the exponential computational power of quantum computers. This abstract dive into the lacunas quantum computers might raise to the now available cryptographic methods applied in block chains, such as public key cryptography, hashing algorithms, and digital signatures. It underlines the urgent nature for the block chain community to work out quantum-proof cryptographic solutions to protect the long-term security of block chain networks. Lastly, this review paper provides a very characteristic view upon the complex and complicated relationship between blockchain, post quantum cryptography and quantum cryptography, showcasing the serious and unraveling need to address security concerns related to transactions and everything that blockchain is involved in while also capitalizing on the vast pool of innovative potential that the convergence of this giant of technical world carry among themselves. The future will definitely be a witness of a dynamic and vibrant interaction of challenges and opportunities discuss further in this review paper as these two future leading giants will continue to shape the digital and cyber world.
ER  - 
