N2  - The Internet of Things (IoT) has revolutionized the way physical devices, appliances, vehicles, and objects interact and exchange data over the Internet. This paper provides a comprehensive overview of IoT, covering its architectural development, deployment, and various application domains such as healthcare, agriculture, industry 4.0, and smart cities. The integration of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) in IoT is also discussed, highlighting the benefits of enhanced data analysis, improved efficiency, and autonomy. The challenges in IoT architecture, including scalability, interoperability, security, privacy, reliability, and low latency concerns are addressed, alongside future trends such as blockchain technology, augmented reality (AR) and virtual reality (VR) integration, quantum computing, and the Internet of Everything (IoE). Overall, this paper provides valuable insights into the current state and future prospects of IoT, making it a valuable resource to gain meaningful insights.
