N2  - The healthcare industry has undergone rapid evolution in the past few years due to advances in various technologies, such as artificial intelligence, blockchain, the Internet of Things, virtual reality, augmented reality, and quantum computing. The integration of such cutting-edge technologies in the healthcare system has led to the emergence of numerous innovative applications, diverse solutions, and new challenges for healthcare data management, security, privacy, analysis, and delivery. The paper reviews the recent years offering a thorough examination of the research domain surrounding the utilization of these advanced technologies in the healthcare landscape. The comprehensive investigation examines the research context exploring the advantages and applications of the aforementioned technologies, and scrutinizing their impact on the related field like impact in the sector encompassing considerations such as the influence on data privacy, security, usability, and overall transforming effects anticipated upon implementation. Extending to future prospects of the studies, contemplating potential direction, suggestions, and opportunities in the suggested methodologies, ensuring continuous development in healthcare.
