N2  - The Internet of Things (IoT) emergence offers the healthcare industry hitherto unheard-of potential. By giving patients access to features like remote monitoring and self-monitoring, IoT devices have already had a significant impact on healthcare services. According to their current health status, patients can utilize IoT to modify their strategies and potential safety measures. The technology enables users to monitor and manage a variety of data, including daily calorie intake, exercise level, reminders for appointments, and blood pressure variations. Future studies must also make clear how healthcare institutions can modernize their internal processes, increase blockchain throughput, and create efficient consensus protocols that satisfy the needs of the Io) and blockchain solutions in the industry.
