N2  - In block chain technology, a distributed architecture, blocks are the data storage and processing unit. Data must be exchanged from one party to another safely and securely, and the block chain must be updated using smart contracts. But still, the problem facing was securing the healthcare data. So, this paper proposed securing health records using the QCNN method, which stands for a Quantum Convolutional Neural Network with Block Chain Technology, to safeguard medical data. Block chain technology's consensus process ensures that all data is correct and all transactions are safe. The datasets are collected from the data world repository. The datasets are pre-processed using label coding with the standard scalar method. The features are analyzed with QCNN and the patient healthcare data to increase the security and interoperability using block chain technology. The research specifically looks at Electronic Health Record (EHR) security issues to be overcome. This proposed quantum conventional neural network (QCNN) deep learning architecture provides higher accuracy and security than the other existing algorithms.
