N2  - The construction of a smart library is an inevitable trend in the era with the emergence and rapid development of the Internet of Things, AioT, big data, cloud computing, mobile Internet, 5G, artificial intelligence, blockchain, and quantum information technology. Librarians, readers, space, literature resources, and reading promotion activities can all be connected to each other through the Internet of Things data technology after building a smart library, and monitor and evaluate the development process. This article not only introduces the face recognition system, book management system, book recommendation and purchase platform, book positioning system, book self-checkout system, reader service reservation system, reader activity management system and librarian attendance system in smart libraries, and also took the innovative and entrepreneurial talent training service carried out by the library of JiLin Agricultural Science and Technology University as an example, expounding how the smart library operates based on the Internet of Things data technology.
