N1  - Export Date: 15 February 2026; Cited By: 7; Correspondence Address: P.T. Shanthala; Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Visvesvaraya Technological University, Bengaluru, PESIT-Bangalore South Campus, Karnataka, India; email: Shanchendu@gmail.com
N2  - Significant progress has been made as a result of the various technology intersections like blockchain, cloud computing, robotics, artificial intelligence, 5G, and big data. A variety of devices have been able to enter the industry thanks to the Internet of Things, which has also made considerable advancements in recent years. Enhanced security measures should be implemented to ensure that user data remains secure. In this research, we propose a novel method termed Improved Faster Recurrent Convolutional Neural Network (RCNN) with a ciphertext comparison-based Homomorphic Encryption (HE) scheme in the realm of the Internet of Things (IoT) to provide enhanced security. The improved faster RCNN is used as the classifier to classify the data points and provide parameters for training the algorithm. Several performance metrics, such as accuracy, runtime, and data transfer rate, are used for evaluation. Our proposed approach provides more data security, a higher accuracy of 99.58%, and a shorter encryption time to encrypt the user’s data, and also reduces computational overheads by using a low data transfer rate.
