N1  - Export Date: 15 February 2026; Cited By: 2; Correspondence Address: K. Sultan; American University of Kuwait (AUK), College of Engineering and Applied Sciences, Salmiya, Kuwait; email: ksultan@auk.edu.kw; Conference name: 21st IEEE International Conference on Smart Technologies, EUROCON 2025; Conference location: Gdynia; Conference date: 2025-06-04 through 2025-06-06; Conference sponsors: Gdynia Maritime University; IEEE Poland Section; IEEE Region 8; IEEE Systems, Man, and Cybernetics Society (SMC); Warsaw University of Technology
N2  - The incredibly fast development of digital technologies including 5G, the Internet of Things (IoT), Artificial Intelligence (AI), and cloud computing has massively increased global interconnectivity, economic development, and social cohesion while simultaneously expanding the attack surface for sophisticated cyber threats. Traditional cybersecurity methods are no longer sufficient to counter the speed, scale, and complexity of modern attacks. This paper addresses these challenges by proposing a forward-looking cyber resilience strategy that integrates AI-driven threat detection and quantum-safe cryptographic techniques. Specifically, we resent: (1) a comprehensive analysis of the evolving cyber threat landscape, including AIpowered attack vectors; (2) an evaluation of emerging technologies such as AI, blockchain, and quantum cryptography in countering these threats; and (3) the conceptual development of an Integration Layer that strategically unifies these technologies into an adaptive, intelligent, and resilient security framework. The potential impact of this approach lies in its ability to guide the design of next-generation cybersecurity systems that are both future-proof and scalable - capable of protecting critical infrastructure, healthcare systems, and financial networks against emerging threats. This work also outlines pathways for empirical validation and alignment with global cybersecurity standards, contributing to the broader effort toward secure and sustainable digital transformation.
