N2  - Sixth generation (6G) wireless communication is the next frontier. Researchers and business professionals are already focusing on the sixth generation of wireless technology, even though 5G is still being deployed globally. What can we anticipate from 6G, then? It's anticipated to be a dramatic advancement over 5G, providing previously unheard-of speeds, extremely low latency, and connectivity that extends well beyond laptops and smartphones. In our future, almost everything will be effortlessly connected; consider augmented reality, IoT gadgets, and more. Artificial intelligence integration is a crucial component of 6G. More effective resource management, improved user experiences, and network performance optimisation are all anticipated to be greatly aided by AI. The integration of AI with wireless communication is predicted to bring in a new age of intelligent, adaptable, and responsive networks. The pathway towards 6G wireless communication networks is thoroughly examined in this study, with an emphasis on possible innovations, difficulties, and game-changing potential. Also, this paper proposes an AI-driven framework for 6G networks, focusing on optimizing resource management, self-healing, and network security. It aims to improve real-time decision-making, reduce latency, and enhance fault recovery using machine learning. Simulations validate the framework's effectiveness and offer scalable solutions for 6G deployment.
