N2  - Global Navigation Satellite Systems (GNSS) play a vital role in today’s digital world by providing accurate positioning, navigation, and timing services. These systems support a wide range of applications including transportation, agriculture, telecommunications, disaster response, and environmental monitoring. This review provides a detailed overview of how GNSS has evolved and how it operates, including its main components and satellite constellations. It also highlights the integration of GNSS with modern technologies such as Artificial Intelligence (AI), the Internet of Things (IoT), 5G, and blockchain, which together enhance system performance and reliability. The paper concludes by examining future trends, including advanced satellite constellations, quantum-based timing, and the increasing accessibility of high-precision GNSS tools. The study affirms GNSS as a strategic enabler of innovation, digital resilience, and global economic advancement.
