N1  - Export Date: 15 February 2026; Cited By: 0; Correspondence Address: P. Girija; Panimalar Engineering College, Dept of IT, India; email: girijapaper@gmail.com; Conference name: 6th International Conference on Electronics and Sustainable Communication Systems, ICESC 2025; Conference location: Coimbatore; Conference date: 2025-09-10 through 2025-09-12
N2  - Pervasive computing brings a new approach to technology that lets devices work on their own and adjust to their surroundings to create experiences that fit user needs. This research study examines all aspects of pervasive computing including its design elements, practical use cases, present-day difficulties, new developments, and remaining unanswered questions. The system works through four architectural layers that make up its infrastructure, networking, middleware, and application elements. Pervasive computing changes how we use services in healthcare, homes, transportation, stores, and schools. Despite showing great potential the widespread use of computing technology deals with power limitations privacy security issues standardization and moral debates. The latest AI technology breakthroughs with 5G, blockchain and sustainable practices solve existing problems and create fresh development opportunities. The discipline is expanding with new research paths that focus on advanced human-computer interaction and quantum computing integration plus ethical standards development. Through smart solutions to existing challenges and new technology advancements pervasive computing will transform how people connect with technology to make intelligent and sustainable spaces for everyone. Our study helps researchers and professionals understand the present situation and future potential of pervasive computing so they can work together across disciplines to achieve its complete benefits.
