N2  - The incorporation of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in the healthcare has transformed patient care, diagnostics, and personalized Medicare in the today's era. As a result, it also increases significant privacy concerns due to sensitive healthcare data. This paper provides the comprehensive review of privacy-preserving methods, including federated learning, homomorphic encryption, differential privacy, blockchain, and secure multiparty computation that analyzing them in terms of privacy guarantees, computational complexity, scalability, and real-time applicability. Future work focuses on developing hybrid frameworks, lightweight privacy solutions for edge computing, and quantum-resistant cryptography to address evolving security threats. These advancements will play the pivotal role in ensuring secure, scalable, and ethically sound AI-driven healthcare systems.
