N2  - This paper studies on data integrity audit and privacy protection in cloud storage. When discussing the possible problems of identity privacy leakage and data tampering in the cloud storage shared data integrity audit scheme, the solution is being proposed to manage the users of the entity permission allocation center to ensure the integrity and security of data and effectively realize identity traceability. At the same time, according to the vulnerability of the traditional cloud storage data integrity verification protocol under quantum attack, a dynamic integrity verification scheme based on lattice and Bloom filter is proposed. This scheme uses lattice theory to solve the small integer solution calculation problem, and combines the Merkel hash tree and Bloom filter to achieve efficient data integrity verification, while ensuring the security and privacy protection of user data. After security proof and performance evaluation, the scheme has a small overhead in storage space and computing time, and meets the goals of security, correctness and feasibility, and effectively resists quantum attacks. This paper aims to provide beneficial exploration and practice for the security and privacy protection in the cloud storage field, and provides new ideas and methods for solving the cloud storage security problem.
