N2  - In a time characterized by the swift transmission of electronic files, the importance of secure and dependable approaches to document authentication has reached unprecedented levels. In the aftermath of the pandemic, individuals have grown increasingly receptive to employing digital resources and have become more dependent on technology, necessitating a departure from the traditional paper-based bureaucracy they have long adhered to. Consequently, the ability to generate a distinct signature for each document holds immense value across various sectors, as it can serve as a means for legally binding agreements or verifying the genuineness of a given document. In this context, our proposal provides users with the capability to maintain trust and confidence in their digital interactions through a transparent and user-friendly solution for verifying document integrity.
