UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0045790624008759
N2  - Due to the intrinsically open, distributed, and highly dynamic nature of Vehicular Ad-hoc Networks (VANETs) and their application scope, the safety and security of VANETs have garnered significant attention both from academics and industry. In this context, among the key security concerns are the Black-Hole Attack (BHA) and Gray-Hole Attack (GHA). In these types of attacks, a malicious node lies in the cyber-physical path, altering a reliable communication route into a compromised one by dropping the packets. In VANETs, these packets carry payload and critical warning alerts. Dropping such important packets can negatively impact VANET's security and performance, potentially leading to road accidents, fatalities, traffic jams, and congestion. In this survey paper, we contributed by conducting a comprehensive exploration of security approaches for mitigating against BHA and GHA in the AODV-based VANET. Beginning with an insightful overview of the background, we further critically reviewed various security attacks in related routing protocols in VANETs and presented them in an organized tabular form. After critically analyzing the detection approaches, we further grouped them into distinct categories based on their methodology and techniques adopted, including cryptographic, IDS, trust-value, clustering, additional means, hybrid, and threshold-based techniques, and tabulated chronology. Furthermore, we implemented and evaluated various mitigation approaches in the NS-2 simulator, allowing for a detailed comparative analysis, and adding recommendations to help in the selection of optimal approaches for improving network security, reliability, and efficiency. This extensive analysis can serve as a valuable resource for researchers and practitioners in the field, highlight some research gaps in VANET security, recommend further studies for novel development with essential guidance and future directions, enhanced resilience, and a comprehensive understanding of the complex and challenging VANET security landscape.
