N2  - The growing complexity and broad adoption of software systems have considerably raised the risk of cyber-attacks and data breaches, underlining the significance of privacy-centric systems that protect sensitive data while staying functional. Privacy measures must be implemented and promoted across the whole software development lifecycle to safeguard users’ sensitive information. This paper summarizes the various data anonymization methodologies, privacy regulations, and security technologies used to design privacy-centric system integrations and architecture. Findings from the review suggest that a focus on privacy-centric system integrations and architecture improves data protection and compliance with laws and regulations and enables the establishment of cybersecurity that combats emerging risks and vulnerabilities. By employing robust privacy measures throughout the software development lifecycle, potential data breaches and unauthorized access can be mitigated to maintain trust among stakeholders.
