N2  - Today the market of mobile networks, which we use like mobile phones, tends towards tremendous sustainable growth, reshaping how individuals and societies interact with mobile computing technologies. Even though, we may still encounter many network security threats due to those disruptive and complicated technologies. This article examines the primary security threats imposed by the open and complex nature of wireless networks (malware attacks, phishing, and man-in-the-middle attacks), and enhances the problem-solving capabilities with the root cause analysis. Also, major mitigations, like data encryption, access control, and firewalls, are employed to reduce these evolving threats in this study with in-depth analysis. Different applications constituting large shares in the market were also introduced, covering everything from social media platforms to productivity tools. In addition to investigating innovations like artificial intelligence, machine learning, and the rise of zero trust architecture, this article also explores the key trends that are shaping the future of network security. This research promises to be a valuable resource, contributing to the theoretical foundation of mobile computing as well as the practical guidance for network security.
