N2  - Nowadays, emerging technologies such as smart terminals, cloud computing, and the Internet of Things are developing rapidly. The”One-to-one” encrypted transmission method is difficult to meet the communication needs in complex network environments due to high computational costs. Broadcast encryption technology can provide data encryption protection during information sharing among multiple users. However, most of the existing schemes are based on bilinear groups, which cannot resist quantum computing attacks. And these schemes also suffer from the key escrow problem. For this reason, a novel distributed broadcast encryption scheme is proposed based on the Learning with Errors (LWE) difficulty assumption on the lattice. The scheme avoids key interaction negotiation among users by introducing a public key bulletin board. Meanwhile, the scheme solves the security problem caused by the authoritative user's complete mastery of the user's private key.
