N2  - The development and innovation of China’s cultural industry (CI) has attracted widespread attention. In recent years, the digital economy (DE) has become a key topic of interest in both society and academia, and the integration of the digital economy with other industries is also underway. This paper focuses on the integration of the DE with CI, collects panel data from 30 provinces and cities in China from 2015 to 2021, selects relevant indicators, measures them using a coupling coordination model, and analyzes the influential factors of their coupling in depth with the Tobit model. The study found that the coupling coordination of China’s DE with CI still needs to be improved, and if necessary, it can be promoted by government policies, information infrastructure, industrial structure, and opening up to the outside world. Based on the current situation of the integration of China’s DE with CI, this article provides relevant suggestions and countermeasures to help its future development.
