N2  - The government of The Philippines is undergoing a digital transformation to make its operations more efficient. Among other programs, the government is migrating to the cloud. This paper addresses the expected developmental impact of this cloud migration initiative. This migration is expected to provide significant benefits in several areas. Benefits encompass both traditional financial measures, as well as intangible benefits, measured both quantitatively and qualitatively. The cloud offers on-demand access to unlimited state-of-the-art computing facilities at lower cost. It replaces capital expenditures with a monthly subscription fee. In essence, it acts as a utility. Other benefits include reduced labor costs, improved productivity, reduced energy costs, faster innovation cycles, economies of scale, and enhanced security, among others. The impact is considered in three categories: macroeconomic and development impacts, economic benefits of cloud computing in the public sector, and potential benefits of the Cloud Center of Excellence.
