N2  - Proof of Authority (PoA) consensus algorithm mainly consists of authorized nodes to participate in each round of consensus, and the information of authorized nodes is public to a large extent, which is prone to problems such as centrality as well as predictive attacks on out-of-block nodes. To this end, this paper proposes a VB-PoA consensus algorithm based on verifiable random functions and BLS aggregated signatures. Firstly, improve the participation of nodes in each round of consensus process, select block nodes from ordinary nodes, and authorize nodes as the verification nodes of each round of consensus to avoid causing centralization. Secondly, a verifiable random function is used to randomly select the blocking nodes for blocking to avoid predictive attacks on the blocking nodes in the consensus. Finally, the aggregated signature algorithm is used to aggregate the verification information into the block header to ensure the security and correctness of the block. The experimental results show that the VB-PoA algorithm has a higher degree of node participation in the consensus process, can correctly and effectively randomly select the block nodes, and has a high degree of security.
