N2  - With the rapid digital transformation in the education sector, traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) higher continuing education faces significant challenges in adapting to the digital era. The existing curriculum models and educational methods do not meet the growing need for digitally skilled TCM professionals. This study addresses these challenges by proposing a “three-dimensional synthesis” model for digital talent cultivation, which includes restructuring the curriculum system, integrating technological tools for practical training, and developing a lifelong learning platform. Using the support vector machine (SVM) algorithm to analyze survey data, we identify key factors influencing learners' digital literacy and professional skills in TCM education. The results show that the proposed model enhances both digital literacy and professional competence, contributing significantly to the modernization of TCM education. The findings provide valuable insights for further digital integration in TCM and offer practical recommendations for its global application.
