N2  - This paper explores the application of data intelligence agents in security protection. It analyzes their practical impact across critical sectors including education, finance, industrial systems, and healthcare. Significant outcomes include improved detection accuracy, sub-second response times, and reduced compliance costs. A tri-layered architecture (encryption/fortification/isolation) and cognitive closed-loop framework are introduced. This framework spans knowledge graphs, deep detection, and reinforcement optimization. Together, they transform traditional passive defense models. This research provides methodological foundations for establishing new paradigms of cognitive collaborative defense in the security industry.
