N2  - With the advancement of technology, research on Artificial Intelligence (AI) in the fields of Information Technology (IT) and Smart City (SC) has garnered increasing attention. Against this backdrop, to unveil the current status and evolution trends of this research, this paper utilizes the Web of Science Core Collection as the search source and employs visualization tools such as CiteSpace 6.2 R7 and VOSviewer to analyze data spanning from January 1, 2005, to October 11, 2024. The research indicates that over the past two decades, the number of publications in this field has shown a gradual upward trend, which can be divided into three stages: the incipient stage, the rapid development stage, and the fluctuating growth stage. China is the country with the highest number of publications, while Yigitcanlar, T., and Jeon, G. are identified as core authors in this field with significant influence. Research hotspots are concentrated on Intelligent Technology Ecology, Intelligent Technology Integration, Smart City Technology, and Intelligent Metropolitan Area Future, among others. The integration of AI, IT, and SC is steadily promoting sustainable urban development, bringing more convenience and opportunities to life. In the future, this research will continue to deepen, explore more areas, and overcome more challenges.
