N2  - Cybersecurity is a focal point of research in cyberspace governance. The rule of law is a critical mechanism for ensuring cybersecurity. This article is based on 3,001 relevant literature from the core collection of the Web of Science (WoS) database. Leveraging the advantages of CiteSpace bibliometric visualization, it generates national / regional maps, author collaboration maps, and conducts keyword analysis to explore research hotspots and dynamics. The research indicates the following: Cyberspace is no longer a lawless territory, but the rapid development of new technologies and emerging cultural media formats in the online domain poses significant challenges to the legislation, law enforcement, and judicial system construction for cybersecurity. The governance of cyberspace security has undergone an evolutionary process from administrative-led governance -event-driven governance -comprehensive governance framework. This study reveals the’technology-institution’ double helix model of evolution law of cybersecurity rule of law research through CiteSpace bibliometrics, providing insights into the direction for future research.
