N2  - With the digital transformation, accounting data quality issues (e.g., duplication, inconsistency) pose significant challenges to enterprise decision-making. This paper presents a computer-aided intelligent evaluation model for accounting data quality, integrating machine learning algorithms (e.g., decision trees, SEM) and blockchain-based traceability technologies within the data governance framework. Through empirical analysis of 130 enterprises and case studies in manufacturing/finance sectors, the research demonstrates that the model enhances data accuracy by 25%-40% and reduces error rates via automated cleaning and real-time monitoring. Key innovations include: (1) a hybrid governance model integrating structural equation modeling and clustering algorithms; (2) blockchain-based data integrity verification system; (3) NLP-driven real-time quality monitoring mechanism.
