N2  - Machine learning can be misled by adversarial examples, which is formed by making small changes to the original data. Nowadays, there are kinds of methods to produce adversarial examples. However, they can not apply non-differentiable models, reduce the amount of calculations, and shorten the sample generation time at the same time. In this paper, we propose a new black box attack generating adversarial examples based on reinforcement learning. By using deep Q-learning network, we can train the substitute model and generate adversarial examples at the same time. Experimental results show that this method only needs 7.7ms to produce an adversarial example, which solves the problems of low efficiency, large amount of calculation and inapplicable to non-differentiable model.
