N2  - Hidden Markov model is a model used to describe a Markov process with hidden unknown parameters. It has been widely used in the fields of finance, computer, artificial intelligence and so on. With the increasing data sets in the financial industry, the traditional hidden Markov model needs more and more parameters and space-time resources to solve the corresponding problems. However, with the development of quantum computing, we combine quantum computing and hidden Markov with the financial industry, and propose a new stock prediction model based on quantum hidden Markov algorithm for the first time. Compared with the hidden Markov model used in the financial industry to predict stock data, adding the quantum version of the hidden Markov model to the stock prediction model can not only verify the credibility of the combination of quantum algorithm and classical algorithm, but also integrate the two probability matrices of AC in the hidden Markov model into the Karus operator with fewer parameters, So as to reduce the use of parameters and achieve the effect similar to the traditional hidden Markov model.
